mistry","section":"A","questionType":"MCQ","questionText":"Of the five isomeric hexanes, the isomer which can give two monochlorinated\ncompounds is ","options":["n-hexane","2, 3-dimethylbutane ","2,2-dimethylbutane","2-methylpentane"],"correctOption":1,"solution":"<img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/bdQKLdM5gvjIGyx2Y/YHWRXzP629SLKBXENHMf9faR7pEzW/5WDK7RhrpObNaI8iXu3sIf/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"AIEEE 2005 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 167 English Explanation 1\"> \n<br><br>Since it contains only two types of $$H$$-atoms hence it will give only two mono chlorinated compounds viz. \n<br><br><img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/Pxx7XOEwbcORvy9LY/xvRPB2yLQsjzoykJaddmyN9ryZjXV/52BR2Yu8mFn6EctThIiIlD/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"AIEEE 2005 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 167 English Explanation 2\"> \n<br><br>and \n<br><br><img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/WEKgt4f5sLwsC0cHL/QC4sRsVNl8eUaE1rQdpFD6mlC92dB/dTL9JvEWrePsybJxHX71bX/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"AIEEE 2005 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 167 English Explanation 3\"> ","marks":4,"negativeMarks":-1,"topic":"Hydrocarbon"},{"id":"Upud2y2sCAOmjWB3","questionNumber":14,"subject":"Chemistry","section":"A","questionType":"MCQ","questionText":"Toluene is nitrated and the resulting product is reduced with tin and hydrochloric acid. The product so\nobtained is diazotised and then heated with cuprous bromide. The reaction mixture so formed\ncontains ","options":["mixture of o\u2212 and p\u2212bromotoluenes ","mixture of o\u2212 and p\u2212dibromobenzenes ","mixture of o\u2212 and p\u2212bromoanilines ","mixture of o\u2212 and m\u2212bromotoluenes"],"correctOption":0,"solution":"<img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/o5dirjyQkx4Udt14x/n0p9vyRwXzqQTCvogOZyjjZD4vVC9/9zRymhZEC8KeVotS8KLkAe/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"AIEEE 2008 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 163 English Explanation 1\"> \n<br><br><img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/yjeOJ1HYbvEzW1GWT/TxzXz3UvM9tFdWwCrbl9uwTzjhEca/WelNNdwPXu8sc5z2hgeIyu/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"AIEEE 2008 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 163 English Explanation 2\"> \n<br><br>on reduction with $$Sn/HCl$$ they will form corresponding anilines in which $$ - N{O_2}$$ group changes to $$ - N{H_2}.$$ \n<br><br><img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/OiXW3YoeZpXQR6lKx/ID2xfzb7WyKwN5eud0PjIbFbk6m72/kykyfvE3fwoWsdRqYSYoZm/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"AIEEE 2008 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 163 English Explanation 3\"> \n<br><br>These anilines when diazotized and then treated with $$CuBr$$ forms $$o-, p-$$ bromotoluenes. ","marks":4,"negativeMarks":-1,"topic":"Hydrocarbon"},{"id":"m6rlxhmd","questionNumber":15,"subject":"Chemistry","section":"A","questionType":"MCQ","questionText":"<p>Identify product [A], [B] and [C] in the following reaction sequence.</p>\n<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{C} \\equiv \\mathrm{CH} \\xrightarrow[\\mathrm{H}_2]{\\mathrm{Pd} / \\mathrm{C}}[\\mathrm{A}] \\xrightarrow[\\text { (ii) } \\mathrm{Zn}, \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}]{\\text { (i) } \\mathrm{O}_3}[\\mathrm{~B}]+[\\mathrm{C}]$</p>","options":["<p>[A]: CH<sub>3</sub>\u2014CH=CH<sub>2</sub>, [B]: CH<sub>3</sub>CHO, [C]: CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>OH</p>","<p>[A]: CH<sub>3</sub>\u2014CH=CH<sub>2</sub>, [B]: CH<sub>3</sub>CHO, [C]: HCHO</p>","<p>[A]: CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>3</sub>, [B]: CH<sub>3</sub>CHO, [C]: HCHO</p>","<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m6rluk33/b3a164aa-455b-4a81-8458-f2ecc479aca4/4ee88bf0-e395-11ef-bd37-5bfdd6d633f7/file-jaoe38c1m6rluk34.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m6rluk33/b3a164aa-455b-4a81-8458-f2ecc479aca4/4ee88bf0-e395-11ef-bd37-5bfdd6d633f7/file-jaoe38c1m6rluk34.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;d